Secondly they were a little over half full. Still okay at this point when we sipped them we realized we had two cups of Luke warm milk. They were barely a light light tan color, more white. Called their manager(early afternoon on new year day) why I told him the problem he was talking to employees. He says he's sorry but he cant help me because I dont have a receipt.  He hadn't asked me if I had one , he knew because they dont give them to you. I had milk at home didn't need to walk three blocks to pay 11 bucks for it. I would stop drinking them if this was the last place to get a latte. Don't know if it's Starbucks in general or this Starbucks but stay way clear of this one.

If I could give 0 stars overall I would!! I went through a horrible & disgusting incident 2 weeks ago.  I walked in as usual said hello to the cashier/employee as I usually do. Then, I began to tell her my order when all of a sudden she takes out her lipgloss right in the middle of me telling her my order & starts putting it on as if I was her mirror! The audacity this girl has I swear! I couldn’t believe it! She was even fixing it with her fingers so disgusting & unsanitary! In what world would she think that this would be okay to do? Furthermore, what kind of employees are they hiring? Thankfully, she didn’t make my drink but I should have spoken up right away about it. I think the shock of it left me speechless! I eventually let the supervisor who on was duty that day know about this before I left. My interaction with him was satisfactory but as for the manager that’s another story...  I called the next day to speak to the manager Liz since she wasn’t in the day that I went. I told her what happened. She did agree that it was bad & she said she would have a “talk with this employee” & that she is new & young basically letting her off the hook very easily. Quite frankly, I feel that she should be fired for this. Who knows if the employee did what she did on purpose she probably did. Liz said that she didn’t do it on purpose how can she know that for sure. I’m not one to say to fire someone so lightly but this was completely unacceptable! And I’m not just saying this because it happened to me. If I was in charge she would be fired. I asked Liz—“what kind of people are you hiring & to train your employees better” & she says to me not to “insult that employee”. Ugh yeah I was insulting her because I said what kind of employees are you hiring—get the heck out of here! Plus, I just went through a bad experience but what I said was justified. Liz also said to me that “well there are other starbucks in the neighborhood if you don’t want to come here anymore”. Oh really that’s news to me! I also wanted to go there & talk to the employee & Liz at the same time as well but Liz declined. She wasn’t very helpful & I didn’t appreciate her attitude about the situation that is for sure! By the way, I called starbucks customer service & told them all about this. They said that they would escalate this situation to the district manager, Raymond. Hopefully he does something about this but a friend of mine had an interaction with him once & said that he wasn’t helpful so well that’s that.  I would also like to comment that I have felt bad vibes from some of the employees there as well. God is my witness, I walk in there & I’m polite as can be but I’ve still felt those bad vibes from certain employees and I’m pretty sure I know why. I have very dark circles under my eyes and unfortunately lots of people(not everyone thankfully) treat me bad because of it. They think they know me meanwhile they don’t know anything about me! They judge a book by it’s cover. I would like to give those employees of this starbucks a special shoutout for treating me this way! I hope your proud of your ignorant mean selves I truly do! In the words of a Taylor Swift song~~”Maybe I got mine but you’ll all get yours”. It’s called karma!!
